#191

- Growing scattered terrestrially among moss along trail on northeast-facing slope in open mixed oak/hickory woodland, near edge.

Smell: pleasant and sweet.
Taste: not distinctive.
KOH: turning surfaces tannish-brown.

- Returned later and added more pictures and gathered more specimens. (7/25)
